1
00:00:00,968 --> 00:00:02,403
♪

2
00:00:02,436 --> 00:00:04,138
Killua: It’s the tenth day.

3
00:00:04,171 --> 00:00:06,073
Bisky: If they
don’t get back here soon,

4
00:00:06,106 --> 00:00:08,542
then all of their data
is going to be erased.

5
00:00:08,575 --> 00:00:10,177
Killua: Right.

6
00:00:10,210 --> 00:00:13,146
We’ll just have to wait
for goreinu to contact us.

7
00:00:13,180 --> 00:00:14,548
( Gon clicks timer )

8
00:00:14,581 --> 00:00:16,049
Yes! Got it!

9
00:00:16,083 --> 00:00:18,452
Hey, check it out!
I’ve got this down.

10
00:00:18,485 --> 00:00:21,288
Can I start to concentrate
on emitter training now?

11
00:00:21,321 --> 00:00:22,522
Bisky: No way!

12
00:00:22,556 --> 00:00:24,091
Killua: You might have
gotten pretty close,

13
00:00:24,124 --> 00:00:26,193
but you’re still off
by a tenth of a second.

14
00:00:26,226 --> 00:00:28,628
Bisky: Your goal is to be
within a hundredth of a second.

15
00:00:28,662 --> 00:00:29,997
Now begin!

16
00:00:30,030 --> 00:00:32,032
( Gon groans )

17
00:00:32,065 --> 00:00:33,500
( Binder chimes )

18
00:00:33,534 --> 00:00:34,668
Attention.

19
00:00:34,701 --> 00:00:38,104
Another player
has cast contact on you.

20
00:00:38,138 --> 00:00:40,007
( All gasp )

21
00:00:40,040 --> 00:00:41,008
♪

22
00:00:41,041 --> 00:00:42,743
( Singing in Japanese )

23
00:01:24,751 --> 00:01:26,753
♪

24
00:01:29,790 --> 00:01:33,060
Goreinu: It’s goreinu.
Sorry for the wait.

25
00:01:33,093 --> 00:01:34,528
Killua: What’s going on?

26
00:01:34,561 --> 00:01:37,097
Goreinu: It’s been
almost 240 hours

27
00:01:37,130 --> 00:01:39,265
since team tsezguerra left,
right?

28
00:01:39,299 --> 00:01:40,367
Killua: Yeah.

29
00:01:40,400 --> 00:01:42,335
Goreinu: I can
tell you right now

30
00:01:42,369 --> 00:01:43,470
they won’t be returning.

31
00:01:43,504 --> 00:01:45,239
Killua: Why not?

32
00:01:45,272 --> 00:01:47,775
Genthru’s team has started
camping out at the start point.

33
00:01:47,808 --> 00:01:51,779
We decided beforehand that they
wouldn’t return to the game

34
00:01:51,812 --> 00:01:53,747
until I sent him an all-clear.

35
00:01:53,780 --> 00:01:56,182
It was something
of a safety precaution.

36
00:01:56,216 --> 00:01:57,417
Bisky: Understood.

37
00:01:57,451 --> 00:01:59,620
But their card data
will disappear, right?

38
00:01:59,653 --> 00:02:02,356
Goreinu: I’m holding on
to all the cards of value.

39
00:02:02,389 --> 00:02:03,824
Killua: Doesn’t that
just make it obvious

40
00:02:03,857 --> 00:02:05,559
that they have allies?

41
00:02:05,592 --> 00:02:09,229
They’ll notice none of the four
have anything important.

42
00:02:09,263 --> 00:02:10,564
( Goreinu chuckles )

43
00:02:12,399 --> 00:02:15,636
Genthru: They left the game
at 3:05 10 days ago.

44
00:02:15,669 --> 00:02:17,137
Isn’t that right?

45
00:02:17,171 --> 00:02:19,273
Sub: Yeah.
Only five more minutes

46
00:02:19,306 --> 00:02:21,341
’til their card data’s
completely wiped.

47
00:02:21,375 --> 00:02:23,077
They’ve basically quit.

48
00:02:23,110 --> 00:02:26,447
Genthru: We’ll wait
until 3:10 just to be safe.

49
00:02:26,480 --> 00:02:29,817
Bara: All right, but do you
really think they’ve given up?

50
00:02:29,850 --> 00:02:31,385
Genthru: Absolutely.

51
00:02:31,418 --> 00:02:34,421
Why else would they
take off with battera and run?

52
00:02:34,454 --> 00:02:36,790
Sub: It looks like it was
just a desperate attempt

53
00:02:36,823 --> 00:02:38,758
to keep us from getting
the reward money.

54
00:02:38,792 --> 00:02:41,695
Bara: Maybe you’re right,
but those guys have spent years

55
00:02:41,728 --> 00:02:43,330
collecting those 96 cards.

56
00:02:43,363 --> 00:02:45,866
Besides, why would battera
call off his guards?

57
00:02:45,899 --> 00:02:48,201
It doesn’t make any sense to me.

58
00:02:48,235 --> 00:02:50,537
Sub: Yeah, but so what?
Something probably happened.

59
00:02:50,571 --> 00:02:54,141
Genthru: Well, there’s no point
in speculating about it now.

60
00:02:54,174 --> 00:02:56,543
Oh, look. 3:10 already.

61
00:02:56,577 --> 00:02:58,446
Time’s up, I guess.

62
00:02:58,478 --> 00:02:59,746
Sub and bara: Yeah!

63
00:02:59,780 --> 00:03:01,682
Bye-bye, tsezguerra!

64
00:03:02,716 --> 00:03:03,684
Killua: Fake?

65
00:03:03,717 --> 00:03:05,285
Goreinu: That’s right.

66
00:03:05,319 --> 00:03:08,122
We switched several
of their cards with fakes ones,

67
00:03:08,155 --> 00:03:11,225
about 30 of the total 96
of them they have.

68
00:03:12,292 --> 00:03:14,694
I’m actually holding the 96.

69
00:03:14,728 --> 00:03:16,463
For such a cautious guy,

70
00:03:16,497 --> 00:03:18,833
this is the biggest gamble
of tsezguerra’s life,

71
00:03:18,866 --> 00:03:21,736
so I just want to make sure
it pays off.

72
00:03:21,768 --> 00:03:24,504
And i’m really sorry,
but i’m not gonna be able

73
00:03:24,538 --> 00:03:26,473
to help you guys
face team genthru.

74
00:03:26,507 --> 00:03:27,775
Killua: No problem,

75
00:03:27,808 --> 00:03:31,378
but when do you want us
to give you the card?

76
00:03:31,411 --> 00:03:33,847
Goreinu: We can wait
until you’ve defeated genthru.

77
00:03:33,881 --> 00:03:34,849
Good luck, okay?

78
00:03:34,882 --> 00:03:35,850
( Boys grunt )

79
00:03:35,883 --> 00:03:37,318
( Bisky grunts )

80
00:03:37,351 --> 00:03:40,187
Genthru: Now we’ll
go after those brats.

81
00:03:40,220 --> 00:03:41,388
It wasn’t in the plan,

82
00:03:41,421 --> 00:03:43,657
but we can get strip of beach
from them

83
00:03:43,690 --> 00:03:45,192
without too much trouble.

84
00:03:45,225 --> 00:03:47,961
Sub: But first we need
more copies of accompany.

85
00:03:47,995 --> 00:03:48,996
Bara: Okay.

86
00:03:50,631 --> 00:03:51,832
Goreinu: They’re on the move.

87
00:03:51,865 --> 00:03:53,700
Hey, where are
you guys right now?

88
00:03:53,734 --> 00:03:55,369
Killua: Near soufrabi.

89
00:03:55,402 --> 00:03:57,437
Goreinu: Looks like they’re
all heading to masadora,

90
00:03:57,471 --> 00:03:59,606
and as soon as they’ve
got everything ready,

91
00:03:59,640 --> 00:04:01,142
i’m sure
they’ll be coming for you.

92
00:04:01,175 --> 00:04:02,376
Are you ready?

93
00:04:02,409 --> 00:04:03,844
Killua: All set here.

94
00:04:03,877 --> 00:04:06,546
You’ve all been a big help.
Thanks.

95
00:04:06,580 --> 00:04:08,282
Bisky: We need more time,

96
00:04:08,315 --> 00:04:12,486
but we have no choice.
It’s up to gon now.

97
00:04:12,519 --> 00:04:13,487
Gon!

98
00:04:13,520 --> 00:04:15,222
Did you let our conversation

99
00:04:15,255 --> 00:04:18,458
distract you
from your current objective?

100
00:04:18,492 --> 00:04:19,493
( Gon chuckles )

101
00:04:23,564 --> 00:04:25,900
Tsezguerra: Just tell me
what this is about.

102
00:04:25,933 --> 00:04:28,302
I hope you’ll forgive me,

103
00:04:28,335 --> 00:04:31,338
but I took the Liberty
of picking this up.

104
00:04:32,739 --> 00:04:34,874
Is this your daughter?

105
00:04:34,908 --> 00:04:36,910
Or granddaughter, perhaps?

106
00:04:39,947 --> 00:04:41,715
Battera: She was my lover.

107
00:04:41,748 --> 00:04:42,916
Men: Huh?

108
00:04:42,950 --> 00:04:46,620
Battera: She’d been
in the hospital.

109
00:04:46,653 --> 00:04:49,856
She’d been comatose
for some time.

110
00:04:49,890 --> 00:04:54,495
A few days ago,
she passed away in her sleep.

111
00:04:55,596 --> 00:04:58,265
I suppose it was because

112
00:04:58,298 --> 00:05:00,934
she didn’t want people to think
she was only after my money,

113
00:05:00,968 --> 00:05:05,306
but she returned every
expensive gift I gave her...

114
00:05:06,807 --> 00:05:08,876
Every single one,

115
00:05:08,909 --> 00:05:13,313
but she loved this picture frame
I clumsily made myself.

116
00:05:13,347 --> 00:05:15,349
♪

117
00:05:17,017 --> 00:05:20,320
All we ever needed
was each other,

118
00:05:20,354 --> 00:05:23,757
and we swore that we
would never be apart.

119
00:05:27,594 --> 00:05:29,563
Until the accident,

120
00:05:29,596 --> 00:05:33,700
when she fell into a deep sleep,
never to awaken again.

121
00:05:36,837 --> 00:05:38,372
Honestly...

122
00:05:41,308 --> 00:05:42,643
She just...

123
00:05:42,676 --> 00:05:45,779
Looked like she
was only sleeping.

124
00:05:48,048 --> 00:05:52,586
And it was then that I first
heard about "greed island."

125
00:05:54,021 --> 00:05:56,790
If I could only beat that game,

126
00:05:56,823 --> 00:05:59,793
I could obtain
the one item I needed most.

127
00:05:59,826 --> 00:06:02,028
It was like a dream come true.

128
00:06:03,497 --> 00:06:05,466
I was fully prepared

129
00:06:05,499 --> 00:06:09,970
to spend my entire fortune
on copies of that game.

130
00:06:12,005 --> 00:06:15,842
But now it’s all over.

131
00:06:15,876 --> 00:06:18,379
It doesn’t matter anymore.

132
00:06:22,616 --> 00:06:23,917
( Birds chirping )

133
00:06:23,951 --> 00:06:27,354
Genthru: The brats
have four copies of accompany.

134
00:06:27,387 --> 00:06:29,823
We have six ourselves. Ready?

135
00:06:29,857 --> 00:06:30,825
Sub: Hell, yeah.

136
00:06:30,858 --> 00:06:32,827
Bara: You just say the word.

137
00:06:32,860 --> 00:06:36,397
Genthru: I’ll take the kid
who has the spiky black hair,

138
00:06:36,430 --> 00:06:39,633
assuming that we have
to resort to force, that is.

139
00:06:39,666 --> 00:06:42,736
Sub, take the cat-eyed one,
bara, the girl.

140
00:06:42,769 --> 00:06:43,737
( Bara grunts )

141
00:06:43,770 --> 00:06:46,940
Genthru: Accompany on! Gon!

142
00:06:48,008 --> 00:06:49,943
( All gasp )

143
00:06:49,977 --> 00:06:51,545
Killua: What do you want?

144
00:06:51,578 --> 00:06:53,413
Genthru: No need to be hostile.

145
00:06:53,447 --> 00:06:55,049
Let’s just make a deal.

146
00:06:55,082 --> 00:06:57,851
Killua: With you?
We’re not interested!

147
00:06:58,886 --> 00:07:00,554
Bisky: Right.

148
00:07:00,587 --> 00:07:02,722
Don’t let them notice
we’ve been waiting for them.

149
00:07:02,756 --> 00:07:05,626
They can’t know
we’re fully prepared.

150
00:07:05,659 --> 00:07:07,861
Genthru: It’s not a bad deal,
you know.

151
00:07:07,895 --> 00:07:11,031
In fact, it’s so good that
even tsezguerra agreed to it.

152
00:07:11,064 --> 00:07:12,098
Killua: What is it?

153
00:07:12,132 --> 00:07:13,700
Genthru: Curious now?

154
00:07:13,734 --> 00:07:16,036
Gon: Don’t move!
You can talk from over there!

155
00:07:16,069 --> 00:07:18,505
Bisky: Yes, very good.

156
00:07:18,539 --> 00:07:20,508
We have to make it seem

157
00:07:20,541 --> 00:07:22,843
like we’re weak
and at a disadvantage.

158
00:07:22,876 --> 00:07:25,679
We must try to create
the impression

159
00:07:25,712 --> 00:07:29,849
that we only just arrived here
after being cornered in a chase.

160
00:07:29,883 --> 00:07:32,452
Genthru: It’s actually
surprisingly simple.

161
00:07:32,486 --> 00:07:35,456
We’ll beat the game
on everyone’s behalf.

162
00:07:35,489 --> 00:07:37,725
Then everyone
returns to the real world

163
00:07:37,758 --> 00:07:39,893
and splits battera’s reward.

164
00:07:39,927 --> 00:07:42,096
Killua: I find that
hard to believe.

165
00:07:42,129 --> 00:07:44,531
Genthru: We’ve had
a little change of heart,

166
00:07:44,565 --> 00:07:47,501
and tsezguerra and the others
have already left the game.

167
00:07:47,534 --> 00:07:49,503
Killua: Yeah,
but that still doesn’t prove

168
00:07:49,536 --> 00:07:51,505
that he agreed to your offer.

169
00:07:51,538 --> 00:07:53,106
Genthru: Yes, that’s true.

170
00:07:53,140 --> 00:07:55,075
Then you’d rather...

171
00:07:55,108 --> 00:07:56,109
Die here?

172
00:07:57,611 --> 00:08:00,514
Just shut up,
and give us all your cards.

173
00:08:00,547 --> 00:08:02,716
Otherwise,
we’ll kill all of you!

174
00:08:02,749 --> 00:08:05,619
Killua: Finally showing
your true colors, huh?

175
00:08:05,652 --> 00:08:08,622
Gon: Book! Accompany on!
To soufrabi!

176
00:08:11,091 --> 00:08:12,426
( Genthru chuckles )

177
00:08:12,459 --> 00:08:14,061
Three more times.

178
00:08:18,065 --> 00:08:19,667
Two more times.

179
00:08:22,503 --> 00:08:24,672
Only one more time.

180
00:08:25,706 --> 00:08:28,075
All: Return on! Masadora!

181
00:08:30,444 --> 00:08:31,679
Bara: Masadora?

182
00:08:31,712 --> 00:08:34,048
Are they trying to obtain
more spell cards?

183
00:08:34,081 --> 00:08:35,883
Genthru: They might try to reach

184
00:08:35,916 --> 00:08:37,684
the real world
through the harbor.

185
00:08:37,718 --> 00:08:39,787
Accompany on! Gon!

186
00:08:42,956 --> 00:08:44,458
Bara: They’re not here.

187
00:08:44,491 --> 00:08:46,526
Sub: Are they
concealing their presence?

188
00:08:46,560 --> 00:08:48,062
Genthru: Check the store.

189
00:08:48,095 --> 00:08:51,165
Don’t want them getting
their hands on any spell cards.

190
00:08:52,166 --> 00:08:54,535
Sub: They haven’t been here.

191
00:08:54,568 --> 00:08:56,737
Bara: Maybe they took off
for the harbor.

192
00:08:56,770 --> 00:08:59,139
( Genthru groans )
We have no choice.

193
00:08:59,173 --> 00:09:01,509
Accompany on. Gon!

194
00:09:03,544 --> 00:09:04,545
( Gon yelps )

195
00:09:05,979 --> 00:09:07,881
Genthru: Don’t
lose sight of them!

196
00:09:07,915 --> 00:09:09,750
We’re completely
out of accompanies!

197
00:09:09,783 --> 00:09:11,752
( Running footsteps )

198
00:09:13,787 --> 00:09:14,788
( Bisky gasps )

199
00:09:14,821 --> 00:09:17,590
♪

200
00:09:17,624 --> 00:09:19,059
Genthru: Now...

201
00:09:19,092 --> 00:09:22,596
Why don’t you give up
and hand over your cards?

202
00:09:22,629 --> 00:09:25,999
Gon: You’re crazy!
We’ll never let you have them!

203
00:09:26,033 --> 00:09:28,536
Bisky: Everything is
going as planned.

204
00:09:28,569 --> 00:09:30,704
They want to fight us
one on one.

205
00:09:30,737 --> 00:09:33,807
Gon: If you want our cards,
come and get ’em!

206
00:09:33,841 --> 00:09:35,109
Killua: Wait. What?!

207
00:09:35,142 --> 00:09:36,777
Damn it.

208
00:09:36,810 --> 00:09:38,679
Nice. Now we just need

209
00:09:38,712 --> 00:09:41,114
to separate them
little by little.

210
00:09:41,148 --> 00:09:43,550
Bisky, get out of here now!

211
00:09:43,584 --> 00:09:44,618
Bisky: But i--

212
00:09:44,651 --> 00:09:46,219
killua: I said run!

213
00:09:46,253 --> 00:09:47,221
Sub: Stop!

214
00:09:47,254 --> 00:09:48,722
( Bisky gasps )

215
00:09:48,755 --> 00:09:50,257
Bara: You’re not getting away!

216
00:09:50,290 --> 00:09:52,859
Gon: I’m counting on you two.

217
00:09:52,893 --> 00:09:56,697
Genthru: Sorry, kid,
but you’re all mine now!

218
00:10:01,068 --> 00:10:03,170
♪

219
00:10:06,807 --> 00:10:08,175
( Knuckles crack )

220
00:10:08,208 --> 00:10:09,776
Genthru: So tell me,

221
00:10:09,810 --> 00:10:12,780
you do know that i’m
the bomber, don’t you?

222
00:10:12,813 --> 00:10:15,749
Gon: I heard it from tsezguerra.

223
00:10:15,782 --> 00:10:18,852
Genthru: Oh? I see.

224
00:10:18,886 --> 00:10:21,589
And who told you
how my ability works, then?

225
00:10:21,622 --> 00:10:22,623
( Gon gasps )

226
00:10:22,656 --> 00:10:24,124
Incredible.

227
00:10:24,157 --> 00:10:26,593
All it took
was that one moment,

228
00:10:26,627 --> 00:10:31,232
and he figured out
exactly why i’m so wary and why.

229
00:10:31,265 --> 00:10:34,201
That can only come
from battle experience.

230
00:10:34,234 --> 00:10:37,204
Genthru: Not many too people
know of my ability

231
00:10:37,237 --> 00:10:41,241
and even fewer who have survived
long enough to tell anyone.

232
00:10:41,275 --> 00:10:43,844
- Gon: Book!
- Genthru: Eh?

233
00:10:43,877 --> 00:10:46,580
Gon: I can’t let him
take control.

234
00:10:46,613 --> 00:10:48,582
Look, I really hate the idea

235
00:10:48,615 --> 00:10:51,118
of taking cards
from other people by force,

236
00:10:51,151 --> 00:10:54,821
so promise me right now,
whichever of us surrenders first

237
00:10:54,855 --> 00:10:58,592
has to give up all his cards
to the winner, okay?

238
00:10:58,625 --> 00:11:01,228
Genthru: I think you
might have the wrong idea.

239
00:11:01,261 --> 00:11:03,797
You’re in no position
to be making demands.

240
00:11:03,831 --> 00:11:06,167
Gon: I’m not gonna bend
on this one.

241
00:11:06,200 --> 00:11:08,703
Without a promise,
this is highway robbery.

242
00:11:08,735 --> 00:11:11,805
I’d rather die
than give my cards to a thief!

243
00:11:11,839 --> 00:11:15,009
Kill me if you want to!
I won’t open my binder again!

244
00:11:16,310 --> 00:11:18,179
Genthru: You’re a real lunatic,

245
00:11:18,212 --> 00:11:21,182
but not the same kind
of crazy like me.

246
00:11:21,215 --> 00:11:23,284
All right, I promise, then.

247
00:11:23,317 --> 00:11:24,885
And book.

248
00:11:24,918 --> 00:11:27,854
I’m holding 131 cards.

249
00:11:27,888 --> 00:11:30,858
97 are specified-slot cards.

250
00:11:30,891 --> 00:11:32,726
Gon: I have 102.

251
00:11:32,759 --> 00:11:35,962
As for specified slots,
i’ve got 71.

252
00:11:35,996 --> 00:11:37,731
And book.

253
00:11:37,764 --> 00:11:40,600
Genthru: You have
2 and 75, right?

254
00:11:40,634 --> 00:11:41,768
Gon: Yeah.

255
00:11:41,802 --> 00:11:42,836
Genthru: Book.

256
00:11:44,304 --> 00:11:46,039
That’s all I need.

257
00:11:51,011 --> 00:11:52,946
Good ren...

258
00:11:54,314 --> 00:11:58,785
But it’s clear he still
has a long way to go.

259
00:11:58,819 --> 00:12:00,187
( Gon gasps )

260
00:12:00,220 --> 00:12:01,688
( Grunts )

261
00:12:01,722 --> 00:12:02,990
( Yells )

262
00:12:03,023 --> 00:12:05,025
Bisky: The best defense
is a strong offense,

263
00:12:05,058 --> 00:12:07,627
and besides, a single explosion

264
00:12:07,661 --> 00:12:09,696
won’t be enough
to finish you off...

265
00:12:10,731 --> 00:12:12,766
So stay on the attack.

266
00:12:12,799 --> 00:12:15,035
♪

267
00:12:18,672 --> 00:12:20,340
Genthru: This kid has skill,

268
00:12:20,374 --> 00:12:23,811
but his use of aura
is sloppy at best.

269
00:12:25,078 --> 00:12:27,948
I can’t imagine
why he was so confident.

270
00:12:29,950 --> 00:12:32,853
Bisky: You’re not
on his level at this point.

271
00:12:32,886 --> 00:12:35,989
You won’t be able
to do much damage,

272
00:12:36,023 --> 00:12:37,791
but keep attacking anyway.

273
00:12:41,328 --> 00:12:43,897
You will get hurt.

274
00:12:47,334 --> 00:12:49,903
Genthru: You still
haven’t answered my question.

275
00:12:49,937 --> 00:12:53,073
Who told you about my ability?

276
00:12:53,106 --> 00:12:54,307
( Gon gasps )

277
00:12:54,341 --> 00:12:56,176
Genthru:
Well, it’s not important.

278
00:12:56,210 --> 00:12:58,112
What I want to say is...

279
00:12:58,145 --> 00:13:02,249
That I don’t need to use
my ability to deal with you.

280
00:13:03,884 --> 00:13:05,219
♪

281
00:13:05,252 --> 00:13:06,854
Gon: Exactly as planned.

282
00:13:06,887 --> 00:13:09,957
Bisky: Once he’s seen
how much stronger he is,

283
00:13:09,990 --> 00:13:13,393
we’ll reel him in
and spring the trap.

284
00:13:13,427 --> 00:13:15,195
Gon: Osu!

285
00:13:15,229 --> 00:13:18,399
( Thinking )
That’s how i’d like to respond,

286
00:13:18,432 --> 00:13:22,002
but I don’t wanna be
on the losing end forever.

287
00:13:23,871 --> 00:13:28,008
I’ll make him use his power
and finish the plan later.

288
00:13:28,041 --> 00:13:31,411
Genthru: Hmm.
Looking to get hurt some more?

289
00:13:44,992 --> 00:13:46,327
( Gon groans )

290
00:13:48,762 --> 00:13:50,130
( Genthru gasps )

291
00:13:50,164 --> 00:13:52,166
Gon: Use your ability,

292
00:13:52,199 --> 00:13:54,134
’cause i’ve got
a surprise for you.

293
00:13:54,168 --> 00:13:57,271
Genthru: I know
what you’re thinking...

294
00:13:57,304 --> 00:13:58,872
And I won’t use it.

295
00:14:08,081 --> 00:14:09,449
Damn brat.

296
00:14:15,088 --> 00:14:17,457
Bara: She’s a lot faster
than I thought.

297
00:14:18,525 --> 00:14:20,093
Bisky: Book!

298
00:14:20,127 --> 00:14:23,497
Bara: She should be
all out of transport spells.

299
00:14:23,530 --> 00:14:26,099
What’s she doing?

300
00:14:26,133 --> 00:14:29,503
She used transform
to disguise it as another card?

301
00:14:29,536 --> 00:14:32,906
Bisky: Accompany on!
To soufrabi!

302
00:14:32,940 --> 00:14:35,276
Bara: Accompany?! Why?

303
00:14:43,917 --> 00:14:45,519
I don’t get it.

304
00:14:45,552 --> 00:14:48,755
Why did you go to all
that trouble just for this?

305
00:14:48,789 --> 00:14:51,358
Did you want to be
alone with me or what?

306
00:14:51,391 --> 00:14:54,828
Bisky: Oh, no.
It’s quite simple, really.

307
00:14:54,862 --> 00:14:57,498
I didn’t want you begging
your little friends for help.

308
00:14:57,531 --> 00:15:00,267
Bara: Huh? What the hell
are you talking about?

309
00:15:00,300 --> 00:15:01,835
Bisky: Idiot.

310
00:15:01,869 --> 00:15:05,272
What i’m saying
is that i’m stronger than you.

311
00:15:07,074 --> 00:15:08,075
( Bara yelps )

312
00:15:13,080 --> 00:15:15,249
Why, you little--

313
00:15:25,225 --> 00:15:27,494
( Chuckles )

314
00:15:27,528 --> 00:15:29,263
So you call those attacks, huh?

315
00:15:29,296 --> 00:15:32,299
Well, too bad,
’cause you still can’t beat me!

316
00:15:36,403 --> 00:15:40,507
Bara: I won’t go easy on you.
It’s nothing personal.

317
00:15:40,541 --> 00:15:41,976
( Bisky giggles )

318
00:15:42,009 --> 00:15:44,078
That’s exactly
what I was going to say.

319
00:15:44,111 --> 00:15:46,180
Bara: Huh? Wha?

320
00:15:46,213 --> 00:15:49,416
Bisky: I always
let people get a hit in,

321
00:15:49,449 --> 00:15:50,917
like a tribute,

322
00:15:50,951 --> 00:15:53,187
( voice deepening )
Because once I turn back,

323
00:15:53,220 --> 00:15:56,390
I have a hard time
restraining myself.

324
00:15:56,423 --> 00:15:57,991
( Bara gasps, groans )

325
00:15:58,025 --> 00:16:01,395
Bisky: So I end up
killing my opponents.

326
00:16:08,569 --> 00:16:10,104
( Bara groaning )

327
00:16:10,137 --> 00:16:13,907
Bisky: Oh, are you still alive?
I’m impressed.

328
00:16:13,941 --> 00:16:15,443
Bara: Why would you...

329
00:16:15,475 --> 00:16:17,510
Hide your power if...

330
00:16:17,544 --> 00:16:19,813
You’re that strong?

331
00:16:19,847 --> 00:16:21,148
Bisky: Two reasons.

332
00:16:21,181 --> 00:16:23,483
First, never show your hand,

333
00:16:23,517 --> 00:16:27,488
and second, I absolutely
despise my appearance.

334
00:16:27,521 --> 00:16:30,257
I’m too buff, and I hate it.

335
00:16:30,290 --> 00:16:33,126
So do you agree, or don’t you?

336
00:16:33,160 --> 00:16:35,095
Hmm?

337
00:16:36,430 --> 00:16:38,299
Guess he passed out.

338
00:16:40,133 --> 00:16:42,102
( Running footsteps rustling )

339
00:16:44,338 --> 00:16:46,173
Killua: I’ve got a slight edge

340
00:16:46,206 --> 00:16:48,275
in martial arts skill
and physical strength,

341
00:16:48,308 --> 00:16:51,011
but he has me beat
in aura capacity,

342
00:16:51,044 --> 00:16:53,647
so I probably
won’t be able to hurt him

343
00:16:53,680 --> 00:16:55,215
with any normal attack.

344
00:16:55,249 --> 00:16:58,119
That makes him perfect
to experiment on.

345
00:16:58,151 --> 00:16:59,653
♪

346
00:17:01,955 --> 00:17:06,460
Damn it. That hit just felt
like a knife in my brain.

347
00:17:06,493 --> 00:17:09,062
Can’t afford to mess around
with this guy.

348
00:17:12,366 --> 00:17:13,467
( Sub gasps )

349
00:17:17,237 --> 00:17:18,271
Killua: Wrong.

350
00:17:18,305 --> 00:17:20,274
Experiment number one...

351
00:17:21,608 --> 00:17:23,877
Lightning palm!

352
00:17:23,911 --> 00:17:25,579
( Sub groans )

353
00:17:27,114 --> 00:17:29,149
Killua: That wasn’t enough
to knock him out,

354
00:17:29,183 --> 00:17:32,086
but at least I can stun him
for a few seconds.

355
00:17:33,120 --> 00:17:36,123
Okay. Experiment number two.

356
00:17:37,124 --> 00:17:38,492
Sub: A yo-yo?

357
00:17:43,063 --> 00:17:44,131
Killua: Let’s go.

358
00:17:44,164 --> 00:17:46,133
Sub: What is he up to?

359
00:17:46,166 --> 00:17:48,335
♪

360
00:17:50,170 --> 00:17:51,238
( Gasps )

361
00:17:53,273 --> 00:17:55,242
The hell? What’s it made of?!

362
00:17:57,611 --> 00:17:59,313
Killua: It’s my brother’s alloy.

363
00:17:59,346 --> 00:18:01,248
He came up with it himself.

364
00:18:01,281 --> 00:18:03,583
Weighs around 50 kilograms.

365
00:18:03,617 --> 00:18:05,986
Packs a real punch. See?!

366
00:18:16,063 --> 00:18:18,399
Sub: Between the weight
and centrifugal force,

367
00:18:18,432 --> 00:18:20,467
that really stings.

368
00:18:22,669 --> 00:18:25,038
He’s got a habit of leaving
his right flank exposed

369
00:18:25,072 --> 00:18:27,241
when I attack a certain way.

370
00:18:27,274 --> 00:18:31,478
If I could take his yo-yo
and leave him empty-handed...

371
00:18:32,713 --> 00:18:35,482
He’s bound to make
the same mistake.

372
00:18:36,517 --> 00:18:37,952
( Killua gasps )

373
00:18:37,985 --> 00:18:40,154
Sub: Gotcha...

374
00:18:40,187 --> 00:18:42,289
Right there!

375
00:18:46,026 --> 00:18:48,595
All right!
Time to crush your ribs.

376
00:18:50,030 --> 00:18:52,299
( Groans )

377
00:18:52,332 --> 00:18:56,303
Killua: Uh-oh. Did I forget
to mention I have two yo-yos?

378
00:18:56,336 --> 00:18:58,605
( Sub groaning )

379
00:19:01,608 --> 00:19:04,044
Killua: Wow.
You’re still conscious?

380
00:19:04,077 --> 00:19:07,180
Hey, old man, did you know
that when you kick me,

381
00:19:07,214 --> 00:19:08,949
you raise up your guard arm?

382
00:19:08,982 --> 00:19:11,251
It’s like you’re making
your own blind spot.

383
00:19:12,486 --> 00:19:14,655
Sub: Wait. He used my blind spot

384
00:19:14,688 --> 00:19:17,658
to pull out another yo-yo
and attack?

385
00:19:17,691 --> 00:19:20,694
Hang on. So that means
that your blocking habit was--

386
00:19:20,727 --> 00:19:24,297
killua: Was a fake to make you
kick me with your left leg.

387
00:19:24,331 --> 00:19:26,567
Sub: And when you released
your first yo-yo...

388
00:19:26,600 --> 00:19:30,404
Killua: Yeah. I knew you picked
something up to throw at me.

389
00:19:30,437 --> 00:19:33,707
Sub: Why’d you use accompany
to draw me away?

390
00:19:33,740 --> 00:19:35,508
Killua: To make you focus
on a one-on-one fight

391
00:19:35,542 --> 00:19:37,511
and dismiss your surroundings.

392
00:19:37,544 --> 00:19:40,080
Sub: I just don’t believe it.

393
00:19:40,113 --> 00:19:44,117
In that brief exchange, you had
enough time to set three traps?

394
00:19:44,151 --> 00:19:45,352
Killua: Three, huh?

395
00:19:45,385 --> 00:19:47,120
You gotta be kidding me.

396
00:19:47,154 --> 00:19:49,423
Every move I made was a trap.

397
00:19:50,657 --> 00:19:53,727
( Sub screams )

398
00:19:54,761 --> 00:19:57,130
Killua: Experiment complete.

399
00:19:57,164 --> 00:19:58,799
Looks like they both work.

400
00:20:00,300 --> 00:20:01,501
( Blows landing )

401
00:20:01,535 --> 00:20:02,536
( Gon groans )

402
00:20:04,104 --> 00:20:05,072
Genthru: It’s over.

403
00:20:05,105 --> 00:20:06,673
Why don’t you accept it?

404
00:20:06,707 --> 00:20:09,677
You will never defeat me.

405
00:20:09,710 --> 00:20:12,079
Gon: Shut up.

406
00:20:12,112 --> 00:20:14,081
I’m not...

407
00:20:14,114 --> 00:20:15,849
Finished with you yet.

408
00:20:15,883 --> 00:20:18,085
♪

409
00:20:18,118 --> 00:20:21,488
Genthru: It seems I was wrong.

410
00:20:22,523 --> 00:20:25,159
I take back what I said before.

411
00:20:25,192 --> 00:20:26,727
You are tough.

412
00:20:29,730 --> 00:20:31,665
This is my ability.

413
00:20:31,698 --> 00:20:33,600
I’ll show it to you.

414
00:20:36,436 --> 00:20:39,606
( Thinking ) This battle
isn’t only about the physical.

415
00:20:39,640 --> 00:20:41,876
I’m going to crush his spirit,

416
00:20:41,909 --> 00:20:47,348
his will to fight,
to stand, and to resist.

417
00:20:47,381 --> 00:20:50,918
Otherwise,
he’ll never admit defeat.

418
00:20:50,951 --> 00:20:55,389
If I truly want to win,
I can’t be stubborn.

419
00:20:55,422 --> 00:20:56,890
I’ll make him see.

420
00:20:56,924 --> 00:21:00,194
I’ll prove to him that all
his hard work and confidence

421
00:21:00,227 --> 00:21:03,130
mean absolutely nothing.

422
00:21:03,163 --> 00:21:04,331
Gon: Here it comes.

423
00:21:06,834 --> 00:21:08,436
♪

424
00:21:08,468 --> 00:21:11,504
Narrator: The villain
has unleashed his true power.

425
00:21:11,538 --> 00:21:15,709
Will gon be able
to emerge victorious?

426
00:21:15,742 --> 00:21:17,744
( Singing in Japanese )

